Subject: [PATCH 22/32] PCI: Remove DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE macro use
Patch-mainline: v3.17-rc1
Git-commit: 9baa3c34ac4e27f7e062f266f50cc5dbea26a6c1 (partial)
References: bsc#909580 FATE#317556

We should prefer `struct pci_device_id` over `DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE` to
meet kernel coding style guidelines.  This issue was reported by checkpatch.

A simplified version of the semantic patch that makes this change is as
follows (http://coccinelle.lip6.fr/):

// <smpl>

@@
identifier i;
declarer name DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE;
initializer z;
@@

- DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE(i)
+ const struct pci_device_id i[]
= z;

// </smpl>

[bhelgaas: add semantic patch]
Signed-off-by: Benoit Taine <benoit.taine@lip6.fr>
Signed-off-by: Bjorn Helgaas <bhelgaas@google.com>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb4vf/cxgb4vf_main.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb4vf/cxgb4vf_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb4vf/cxgb4vf_main.c
@@ -2905,7 +2905,7 @@ static void cxgb4vf_pci_shutdown(struct
 #define CH_DEVICE(devid, idx) \
 	{ PCI_VENDOR_ID_CHELSIO, devid, PCI_ANY_ID, PCI_ANY_ID, 0, 0, idx }
 
-static DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE(cxgb4vf_pci_tbl) = {
+static const struct pci_device_id cxgb4vf_pci_tbl[] = {
 	CH_DEVICE(0xb000, 0),	/* PE10K FPGA */
 	CH_DEVICE(0x4800, 0),	/* T440-dbg */
 	CH_DEVICE(0x4801, 0),	/* T420-cr */
